oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Oliver family cabin at Cades Cove
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This photograph shows the Oliver Family Cabin at Cades Cove in the Great Smoky Mountains National Park.

Cades Cove has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places. The National Park Service currently maintains several buildings that are representative of pioneer life in 19th century Appalachia. The John Oliver Cabin was constructed in the 1820s by the cove's first permanent European settlers.
